%N A391971 Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = number of heapable permutations of length n with exactly k 321 patterns.
%C A391971 A permutation of [1..n] is heapable if it can be inserted, one element at a time, into a binary min-heap without violating the heap property.
%C A391971 A 321-pattern in a heapable permutation p = (p(1), p(2), ..., p(n)) is a triad of indices x < y < z where p(z) < p(y) < p(x).
